{{Infobox person | name = Ben Yagoda | image= Ben Yagoda.jpg | caption = speaking at the Third Coast Audio Festival - 21 October 2005 | birthname = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1954|2|22}} | birth_place = [[New York City]], U.S. | death_date = | death_place = | education = [[Yale University]] | occupation = | alias = | title = | family = | spouse = | domestic_partner = | children = | relatives = | ethnicity = | religion = | salary = | networth = | credits = ''[[The New Leader]]'', ''[[The New York Times]]'', ''[[Newsweek]]'', ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' | agent = | URL = }}
'''Ben Yagoda''' (born February 22, 1954) is an American writer and educator. He is a professor of [[journalism]] and English at the [[University of Delaware]].
==Early life== Born in [[New York City]] to Louis Yagoda and the former Harriet Lewis, he grew up in [[New Rochelle, New York|New Rochelle]], [[New York (state)|New York]]. He entered [[Yale University]] to study English in 1971 and graduated in 1976 with a bachelor of arts. He later earned an M.A. in American civilization at the University of Pennsylvania, in 1991.<ref>{{cite web|title=People|url=http://www.english.udel.edu/people/Pages/bio.aspx?i=95|website=Department of English|publisher=University of Delaware|accessdate=19 August 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150906091337/http://www.english.udel.edu/people/Pages/bio.aspx?i=95|archive-date=6 September 2015|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
==Career== He became a freelance journalist for publications such as ''[[The New Leader]]'', ''[[The New York Times]]'', ''[[Newsweek]]'', and ''[[Rolling Stone]]''. He has published a number of books including ''About Town:'' [[The New Yorker]] ''and the World it Made''.
Besides his work as a [[journalism]] and English professor at the [[University of Delaware]], Yagoda also writes occasionally for a ''New York Times'' blog about the English language.<ref>[http://opinionator.blogs.nytimes.com/author/ben-yagoda/ Ben Yagoda blog posts] at ''The New York Times''</ref>
==Personal life== Yagoda resides in [[Swarthmore, Pennsylvania|Swarthmore]], [[Pennsylvania]] with his wife. They have two daughters.
==Selected bibliography== *''[[Will Rogers]]: A Biography'' ([[Alfred A. Knopf]], 1993, {{ISBN|0-394-58512-7}}) *''The Art of Fact: A Historical Anthology of Literary Journalism'' ([[Charles Scribner's Sons|Scribner]], 1997, {{ISBN|0-684-83041-8}}), co-edited with [[Kevin Kerrane]] *''About Town: The New Yorker and the World It Made'' (Scribner, 2000, {{ISBN|0-684-81605-9}}) *''The Sound on the Page: Style and Voice in Writing'' ([[HarperCollins|HarperResource]], 2004, {{ISBN|0-066-21417-3}}) *''When You Catch an Adjective, Kill It: The Parts of Speech, for Better and/or Worse'' ([[Broadway Books]], 2007, {{ISBN|0-767-92077-5}}) *''Memoir: A History'' ([[Riverhead Books]], 2008, {{ISBN|1-594-48886-X}}) *''How to Not Write Bad: The Most Common Writing Problems and How to Avoid Them'' (Riverhead Books, 2013, {{ISBN|1-594-48848-7}}) *''The B-Side: The Death of [[Tin Pan Alley]] and the Rebirth of the Great American Song'' (Riverhead Books, 2015, {{ISBN|1-594-48849-5}})
